title: Zucchini and Corn Tacos
directions: Heat a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add the oil and add in the zucchini, ½ the red onion, minced garlic and corn kernels. Cook for 8-10 minutes until crispy. Season with salt and pepper.
In a small bowl, mash the avocado with lime juice, zest, remaining red onion and jalapeno. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Divide the avocado in ¼ and smash onto warmed tortillas.
Top with zucchini mixture and garnish with cilantro and queso fresco
ingredients: 2 cups zucchini, sliced into ¼" half moons
¼ cup red onion, finely chopped, divided
ADDED: 15 oz can black beans and spinach
Seasoned with black pepper, crushed red, cayenne and cumin
